# Database safety (agents)

- **Never** run destructive or data-mutating database operations in any environment (local, staging, production) unless the user **explicitly approved that exact operation in this chat** (same thread).
- **Do not** run without approval, including: `prisma migrate reset`; `prisma db push` when it could drop data; `db seed` / seed scripts; `DELETE` / `TRUNCATE` / `DROP` / bulk updates; `$executeRaw` / `$executeRawUnsafe` for mutation; `psql` or scripts under `scripts/` that change rows.
- **OK without extra approval:** authoring migration/schema **files** for review; `prisma generate`; read-only queries and read paths in code.
- **Unclear?** Stop and ask before running Prisma CLI, migrations, or any script against a real database.

See [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) § Database safety (agents) for the full policy.
